{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/57578", "id": 244289239, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MjQ0Mjg5MjM5", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/57578", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/57578.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/57578.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/57578", "number": 57578, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "[WIP] HirId-ification", "user": {"login": "ljedrz", "id": 3750347, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM3NTAzNDc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3750347?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz", "html_url": "https://github.com/ljedrz", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ljedrz/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "This is a WIP attempt at complete `HirId`-ification, i.e. deprecating `ast::NodeId`s after the lowering process.\r\n\r\nSadly this can't be done one-by-one, because everything is connected to each other; I added `HirId` to `Hir` nodes, introduced methods working on `HirId` instead of `NodeId` and I'm gradually removing `NodeId`s.\r\n\r\nThis PR currently fails to build `stage1` due to some error on my part, probably in `hir::lowering` or `hir::intravisit`; I would like to get some help with that, and also to know if I have made any \"design flaws\" (e.g. removal of `NodeId` where it will definitely be needed, e.g. by some tool) that haven't revealed themselves just yet.\r\n\r\nCurrent progress on the main hit list (checked ones only have `HirId` now):\r\n\r\n- [x] `hir::AnonConst`\r\n- [x] `hir::Arg`\r\n- [x] `hir::Block`\r\n- [x] `hir::BodyId`\r\n- [x] `hir::Destination` - depends on `hir::Def::Label`\r\n- [x] `hir::Expr`\r\n- [x] `hir::Field`\r\n- [x] `hir::FieldPat`\r\n- [x] `hir::ForeignItem`\r\n- [x] `hir::GenericParam`\r\n- [x] `hir::ImplItem`\r\n- [x] `hir::ImplItemId`\r\n- [x] `hir::Item`\r\n- [x] `hir::ItemId` - `NodeId` used by `syntax::visit::Visitor`\r\n- [x] `hir::Lifetime`\r\n- [x] `hir::Local`\r\n- [x] `hir::MacroDef`\r\n- [x] `hir::Pat`\r\n- [x] `hir::PathSegment` - used in `save-analysis`\r\n- [x] `hir::StmtKind`\r\n- [x] `hir::StructField`\r\n- [x] `hir::TraitItem`\r\n- [x] `hir::TraitItemId`\r\n- [x] `hir::TraitRef`\r\n- [x] `hir::Ty`\r\n- [x] `hir::TypeBinding`\r\n- [x] `hir::VariantData`\r\n- [x] `hir::WhereClause`\r\n- [x] `hir::WhereEqPredicate`\r\n- [ ] `hir::def::Def::Label`\r\n- [x] `hir::def::Def::Local`\r\n- [x] `hir::def::Def::Upvar`\r\n- [x] `hir::map::Entry`\r\n- [x] `hir::map::blocks::ItemFnParts`\r\n- [x] `hir::map::blocks::ClosureParts`\r\n- [x] `hir::map::collector::NodeCollector`\r\n- [x] `hir::map::hir_id_validator::HirIdValidator`\r\n\r\nUntil the HirId-ification is 100% complete the overall code delta will be in plus - this is mostly due to the duplication of some methods working on `NodeId`.\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/50928.\r\n\r\nr? @varkor ", "created_at": "2019-01-13T16:27:14Z", "updated_at": "2019-06-24T19:04:24Z", "closed_at": "2019-02-25T14:21:02Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "872d5c3614a2428e96053a5c343cd951f7ad2bb4", "assignee": {"login": "varkor", "id": 3943692, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5NDM2OTI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3943692?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/varkor", "html_url": "https://